,Recommended,298030,22718287,"Posted: 30 April, 2016",all,Drackbolt,"Back when everyone was playing Starcraft, I was still playing this game.  I couldn't believe more people didn't know how intelligent its design was, how brilliant the waypointing and resource system were.  True, it is not a ""hard counter"" style of play like Starcraft; it is not a click-fest action-RTS hybrid where each unit has a special ability.  It is definitely hard-core RTS with many different build paths, a much deeper tech tree, and much larger armies that are still somehow easy to manage.  So many games and sequels (spiritual and direct) have tried to emulate the ease of play here, but they've all botched it up somehow.  True, it does somewhat boil down to a war of escalation, but it's damn fun every single time getting there.for $5 I'd recommend this to anyone unless you really can't stand RTS games in general."
