,Recommended,298030,32702409,Posted: 23 June,all,joe01489,"Total Annihilation (1997) is a must-play, classic RTS title by Chris Taylor! Two factions, the ARM and the CORE, fight to ensure the complete destruction of the other in multiple story campaigns and battle tactics scenarios. In a skirmish match, your key unit is the Commander, which constructs units in real time using nanolathe technology. Destroy the enemy Commander to defeat the opposing army. This is one of the first RTS games to emphasize the importance of macromanagement in tandem with micromanagement.This game has great replayability. Although I have few hours logged on the Steam version, I have played through every campaign at least twice before buying it on Steam, once on medium difficulty and once on hard. During my medium playthrough, I had logged in a word document over fifty hours of my attempt at a speed run (which does not include failed attempts). Sometimes it is hard to believe that it was released 20 years ago because of its 3D sprites and map layouts, which were way ahead of its time. Total Annihilation is the inspiration for Supreme Commander, also developed by Chris Taylor, which also has a big following.Don't miss out on this gem."
