,Recommended,298030,19832995,"Posted: 21 December, 2015",all,Argoth,"IntroductionOne of the seminal 3D games of the RTS genre, this game was far ahead of its time when released. Total Annihilation still remains peerless in how well rounded it is, from both sequels and rivals.MechanicsThe simplicity of the mechanics is the game's strongest point. All aspects of the game are easy to understand and intuitive. From a clean UI, to satisfying movement and speed of vehicles, the game just feels right. Once you've completed the campaign, skirmishes will entertain for a long time.GraphicsThe visuals still hold up, with solidly modeled machines, angling to accommodate the contours of the landscape - an original feature at release, it still looks convincing to this day. A very complete selection of environment types to choose from, offering varied experiences.SoundThe music of the game is excellent. Sometimes pensively tense, at other times sorrowful, and occasionally stirring with strident pride - but always memorable.ConclusionPerhaps one of the most wholesome RTS games of all time, and certainly one of the most technologically innovative of its time. Own a piece of PC gaming history."
