76561197960800987,Recommended,298030,20597634,"Posted: 17 January, 2016",all,Skho,"Warning: The review below is biased with nostogliaI remember watching a review of Total Annihiliation from one of those 90's ""tech"" shows on cable in my early teens.  I recall being immediately blown away by how fluid and realistic the action was.  I remember the presenter showed an ingame clip of the action depicting a dozen of infantry bots marching haphazardly through a plain with some trees scattered about.  Meanwhile ovehead, three fighters intercepts an incoming enemy bomber.  The fighters fired a salvo of missiles, and barrel rolls away from the explosion of a downed bomber.  EPIC.I brought this game more than 20 years ago.  I've recreated that scene on numerous occasions and then some.  I felt the combination of variety in unit behavior, weapon physic, and the rock/paper/scissor approach to balancing was the epitomy of what real time strategy games are.  Twenty years later, I believe this is still the core defintion that only one other RTS IP was able to achieve, and that's Homeworld.There's Supreme Commander and Planetary Annihiliation, but those are essentially spiritual successors.  Even then, it's still missing something that makes Total Annihilation unique.Plus you have these thingsCarpet bombingAircraft carriersA wall of artillaries shootingFlak gunsEPIC SOUNDTRACKI would buy this again many times over if steam goes away."
