,Recommended,298030,29098053,Posted: 7 January,all,Zefar,An old time classic that still holds up pretty well. With the exception of UI flaws this game is actually able to stand the test of time. Which is quite rare for a RTS game. It'll run on Windows 10 too but some things need to be installed first.So what can you expect? It's an RTS with infinitive resources that needs to be balanced. Metal and Energy. While you have a stock amount of metal and Energy this will quickly go away if you can't keep up with the demand and when it hits bottom things will take far longer to build.The two sides have similar units on Tier 1 but on Tier 2 they vary a bit. But most units can be useful later on. Arm are the best looking though. Just a fact.With mods installed you can build up to 1000 per player but that generally just crashes the game so keep to 500 per player. The AI can't really handle this amount either as they'll do stupid things like building 100 Metal extractors instead of Moho Mines on a metal planet.You'll also get conga lines of enemies towards your base and these lines can be pretty long and pretty big. For instance with 1000 units on that line is just one long line from the enemy base to my base. Or rather to the range of my turrets.There are plenty of unit mods for this game and you'll be needing some programs in order to use them all. But there is still a limit on how many you can have.If you decide to play online you can limit how many units the AI can build of certain things and this can be used to stop them from building a ton of useless structures. Could be a way to make it more of a challenge too.
