,Not Recommended,298030,20280258,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,Ted,"In the game's current state, I can not recommend this game. I tried a multiplayer session with a friend and we could not join each other's game, regardless of who hosted. I was hoping the game code would have been revamped to work on modern operating systems, but that seems to not be the case. It's dependent on DirectPlay, an API that has been deprecated by Microsoft since the early 2000's.edit:At the time we attempted to play this game, my friend and I were on the same local area network (192.168.1.2 to 192.168.1.11). At one point, I did alt+tab out of the game, and added an exception, when prompted, to the Windows Firewall to allow this game to communicate. We were able to see each other's game on the list of games, but when either of us attempted to join the other's hosted game, the interface would lock up and hang indefinitely.My review of not recommending this game is solely based on the game's current state. The networking code is obviously dated and doesn't ""work out of the box,"" requiring tweaking and/or third-party extensions to make it work. This is not what I had in mind when I paid $5 for the Steam version of this game.As far as the game itself, my friend and I had a lot of fun playing this game a decade ago when it worked. So if the game did ""work out of the box,"" I would give this game a thumbs up."
76561197983491531,Not Recommended,298030,19819233,"Posted: 20 December, 2015",all,Junrall,"Loved TA back in the day and was very happy to see it land on Steam. It is one of my all time favorites.The only downside is that there is a glitch when running the game from Steam for the first time. For me it was an easy fix (as described below).If you're ok with doing a one-time workaround, then definitely go purchase this game. Otherwise, I’d wait a little while. The game was recently released and I’m sure it will be fixed fairly soon.So here’s the problem and my fix. Keep in mind that this worked for me and may not work for everyone!Problem:When launching TA for the first time through Steam, I kept getting “Error: Environment initialization failed! Check your DirectX”The Fix:Launched the game directly by running TotalA.exe. This is found in the installation folder:C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Total AnnihilationAfterwards, you should be able to start TA from Steam everytime.If the above does not work, then take a look at Peepswood's post describing how to use these patches:http://steamcommunity.com/app/298030/discussions/0/487877107150113391/If this issue is officialy resolved, then I will change my review to a thumbs up"
