,Recommended,298030,20152601,"Posted: 31 December, 2015",all,Idle: g0dless,"When it was released in 1997 it quickly became apparent how TA was going to be THE genre defining game of the decade, going on to win Gamespot's Game of the Year award that same year.Whether you choose to use lowly k-bots to rush their base, prefer a more elegant appraoch using stealth fighters, or prefer to build an entire line of Big Berthas to long range bomb them into submission there are multiple strategies to winning a battle.Total Annihilation removes the resource gathering, micromanaging aspect of strategy games and instead focuses on combat. War materials are broken into two catagories of either metal or energy, both of which are harvested at a constant rate through each resource generation structure.All in all, TA is my favorite strategy game of all time and I've played countless hundreds of hours blowing up my enemies and securing map domination."
