,Recommended,298030,19831213,"Posted: 21 December, 2015",all,LOOK WHAT YOU MADE ME DOOOOO,"Oh man, this game. This. Game.  From a CD-R of the skirmish disc to a legit big box copy, I invested hundreds if not thousands of hours inTotal Annihilationduring the tail-end of the 90s. Its relaxed pace, expansive map size and tactical variety put the microscopic, tunnel-visioned zerg rush ofStarCraftandRed Alertto shame, the competitor's popularity be damned.My opinion has not changed in the nearly two decades that have passed sinceTotal Annihilation'slaunch date; this is still a forward-thinking masterwork of the RTS genre, its eerily desolate atmosphere and lush, Jeremy Soule-composed score just as evocative as it was back then.Am I biased? Perhaps. Is it perfect? Not at all, but given the time period and meager price tag for what is the definitiveTotal Annihilationexperience? More than worth a revisiting for newcomers and veterans alike."
