,Recommended,298030,21174424,"Posted: 13 February, 2016",all,Lucius,"Pros:- Unit variety is great, there is almost a unit for every conceivable role.- Two resources, metal and energy. Nice and simple, multiple gathering options for each.- Great base defence options, great variety of turrets.- Huge variety of maps, covering multiple terrain types.- Lengthy campaigns, with a great variety of levels.- Soundtrack is epic, with vibrant orchestral pieces- Game comes with all expansions and DLC bundledCons:- AI isn't great. Not idiotic, but does occasionally build navies in small lakes- Battles are often slow-burn affairs as a lot of maps allow for turtling and take time to seize ground, not great for short games.- AI pathing is capable of spectacular failures, getting units stuck.- Scenery (specifically trees) make base building awkward on some maps as getting construction units to remove them is time-consuming and they are often hard to click on.One of the best strategy games ever made. Playing it for the first time in about seven years felt weird, especially because I felt it would have aged worse than it has. Graphics are nothing pretty and visually it has aged badly, but gameplay puts many newer games to shame. Worth the price of admission!"
