,Recommended,298030,28989087,Posted: 3 January,all,Blitzkrieg,"I already own a physical copy of this game. So you are probably thinking: ""Why did you buy it AGAIN?""The answer:It's just that f@$%ing good.I have spent countless hours playing this game, my hours of playing on Steam are only an extremely small fraction of how much I have played this.This game, Halo:CE, Halo 2, Star Wars Battlefront I & II, EAW, and Republic Commando made up a pretty large chunk of my childhood. Total Annihilation is just as good as I remember it. Fun, simple, full of hours upon hours of enjoyment. Of course, being this old, the graphics won't blow you away, and there are bound to be glitches and bugs. It is still extremely fun, and has good LAN support, so if you set everything up correctly and use Hamachi or Tunngle, it would be a very enjoyable experience for you and your friends. There are also many custom maps and units available on sites like TA Universe. Need a giant nuke robot? No problem. Need X-Wings? Of course! Nuke planes? Yep, they have that too. They even have full blown fan-made expansion packs and updates that add numerous new features. All you need to install them is basic computer knowledge.If you want an RTS that isn't overly complicated, extremely fun, has high moddability, can run on really any PC you throw at it? This is your best bet.Would I reccomend this?HELL YEAH."
