76561198142178528,Recommended,298030,21902005,"Posted: 18 March, 2016",all,ddmmkk001,"[Updated]With the latest patch installed from TA Universe, the Steam version of the game runs like it should, and so I've changed my review from negative to positive, and I can recommend the game for purchase. With the latest patch from TA Universe installed, the information below is irrelevant. Make sure you get the latest patch, and NOT one of the archived cracked totalA.exe files for various max unit caps. These don't work with the Steam version of the game.As downloaded from Steam, the game defaults to 250 units and there is no TotalA.ini file, so you'd have to make (or DL) one before you could change to the OTA supported max unit cap of 500 units. However, if this was all you did, then more often than not, the game will crash when both sides are at max units and the fur is starting to fly, and this will happen regardless of whether you have max cap setting of 250 or 500.As soon as I replaced the default version of TotalA.exe with the version of TotalA.exe included in the 1500 unit patch from TA Universe, the game consistently crashed at random times. This happened several times, even though I was within 500 total units at the time. I tried disabling Direct Sound and used Windows sound instead, but the result was exactly the same. Sound isn't the issue.My system is Windows 7 x64bit with a relatively old Nvidia GeForce GTX 750Ti graphics card. I have the latest patch from TA Universe installed and three mods installed. No problems. If you loved TA back in the day, and want it back again, you absolutely can. I also highly recommend using TA Universe as your map and mod source for the game. They've come a long way since the old days, and their site is extensive."
